<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1908-02-17T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1908-02-17T00:00:00-05:00" n="570" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d570">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 10170/7.</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Mexican Chargé</gloss> to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Translation.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">The
                                        Mexican Embassy</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1908-02-17"><hi rend="italic">February 17,
                                    1908</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 138.]</seg></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: With reference to the correspondence
                            exchanged between this embassy and the department in your worthy charge
                            in the extradition case of George Deering Reed, I have the honor to ask,
                            by special <pb facs="0701" n="599" xml:id="pg_599"/> direction of my
                            Government, that the offender be transferred by the authorities of this
                            country to Laredo, Tex., there to be delivered to the agents of my
                            Government duly authorized to receive him.</p>
                        <p>I have pleasure in renewing, etc.,</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">José F. Godoy.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>